  "texts": [
    "Simple pooling functions may not be able to adequately capture the complex structure and relationships of the graph, thus limiting the performance of the model.",
    "In contrast, complex pooling methods provide richer feature representations but may introduce additional computational costs and parameters that increase the risk of overfitting.",
    "Furthermore, many existing graph pooling methods use a fixed pooling strategy, such as selecting a fixed number of nodes or subgraphs for the pooling operation.",
    "However, different graph structures may have different optimal pooling strategies.",
    "Graph pooling methods that lack adaptivity may not be able to extract the most effective features for a specific task or a specific graph structure, thus affecting the performance of the model in a specific application scenario."
  ],
